Description: Fragment of sub-round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine purplish buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Teisagoras. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.18369.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1081)
